=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Learning to Kite spot</span><hr size=1> Not positive at what level this spot should first be tried but i would say about 40.  I know everyone says go to the DL in your 40's, and this spot is in the DL.  On the EQmaps map it is number 10.  Basically it has a 2 spawn of giants in it.  They cycle through all the giants in the zone so con each one till you learn which are which.  If you go to Karnors and go to the southwest corner of the platform, head directly out from that point of the platform.  Right where the ice and dirt meet you will see the little stone hut.  All you have to do is kite them right along the dirt/grass border, heading to the north.  Very few mobs wander through there for adds and you can see them if they are in the way.  Me at 44, I only every once in a while have a green spawn there that is no XP and still have one spawn there that is yellow or red.  An your killing giants so you get the normal giant loot.  The first couple of times when they come running out of that hut carrying a big arse axe or sword it will surprise you.  hehe.  Also they are real fond of this hut.  Meaning if you lose them or have to outrun them or whatever they return to the hut.  Normally you will then find them on top of the hut.  The tunics they drop sell to the merchants for about 60pp each so good loot.<br>
<br>
Orsmo Xlorr<br>
44level Wizard<br>
Prexus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unarach.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Narach</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/23/01 1:04:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> RE: Learning to Kite spot</span><hr size=1> Once you hit level 29, and want to start kiting, a very simply way to practice is go back to the mind teen zones, like nRo, sRo etc. Then just load up your lower DDs, and practise kiting them, this takes away the risk of dying, and you can learn when not to stop and cast etc from the message:<br>
<br>
a dune tarantula tries to hit YOU but misses!<br>
a dune tarantula tries to hit YOU but misses!<br>
<br>
This is how im currently learning how to quad kite, only problem is that you wont know about likely resistances, how hard the mobs hit etc ... but at least you will have had practise before hand.<br>
<br>
Narach<br>
37th Wizard of the Red Wolf Clan<br>
Zeb server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufieht.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fieht</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/27/01 5:53:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RE: Learning to Kite spot</span><hr size=1> A good place to practice Quadding is in LOIO at the broken tower with four Gobs in it dtraight out from the windmill.  They will all be blue and die very quickly.  At 29 I could kill them with 2 bubs of mana left...even with resists.  That is why it is a good place...there are enough resists to keep you on your feet but not enough risk to get you killed (I only died once when I snared myself...hehe...never try to talk and quad)<br>
